Add three new event types and Zod schemas to `packages/shared/src/schemas.ts` for hook lifecycle events, plus extend `ToolCallPartSchema` with a `hooks` field. Also add type re-exports to `packages/shared/src/types.ts`.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add event types to StreamEventTypeSchema enum

In `packages/shared/src/schemas.ts`, add three values to the `StreamEventTypeSchema` enum array (after `'compact_boundary'`):

```typescript
export const StreamEventTypeSchema = z
  .enum([
    // ... existing values ...
    'compact_boundary',
    'hook_started',
    'hook_progress',
    'hook_response',
  ])
  .openapi('StreamEventType');
```

### 2. Add three Zod schemas

Add these schemas after the `CompactBoundaryEventSchema` (currently around line 389):

```typescript
export const HookStartedEventSchema = z
  .object({
    hookId: z.string(),
    hookName: z.string(),
    hookEvent: z.string(),
    toolCallId: z.string().nullable(),
  })
  .openapi('HookStartedEvent');

export type HookStartedEvent = z.infer<typeof HookStartedEventSchema>;

export const HookProgressEventSchema = z
  .object({
    hookId: z.string(),
    stdout: z.string(),
    stderr: z.string(),
  })
  .openapi('HookProgressEvent');

export type HookProgressEvent = z.infer<typeof HookProgressEventSchema>;

export const HookResponseEventSchema = z
  .object({
    hookId: z.string(),
    hookName: z.string(),
    exitCode: z.number().optional(),
    outcome: z.enum(['success', 'error', 'cancelled']),
    stdout: z.string(),
    stderr: z.string(),
  })
  .openapi('HookResponseEvent');

export type HookResponseEvent = z.infer<typeof HookResponseEventSchema>;
```

### 3. Add to StreamEventSchema data union

Add the three new schemas to the `z.union([...])` inside `StreamEventSchema` (after `CompactBoundaryEventSchema`):

```typescript
export const StreamEventSchema = z
  .object({
    type: StreamEventTypeSchema,
    data: z.union([
      // ... existing schemas ...
      CompactBoundaryEventSchema,
      HookStartedEventSchema,
      HookProgressEventSchema,
      HookResponseEventSchema,
    ]),
  })
  .openapi('StreamEvent');
```

### 4. Add HookPartSchema for ToolCallPartSchema extension

Define a `HookPartSchema` for reuse, then add `hooks` field to `ToolCallPartSchema`:

```typescript
const HookStatusSchema = z.enum(['running', 'success', 'error', 'cancelled']);

export const HookPartSchema = z.object({
  hookId: z.string(),
  hookName: z.string(),
  hookEvent: z.string(),
  status: HookStatusSchema,
  stdout: z.string(),
  stderr: z.string(),
  exitCode: z.number().optional(),
});

export type HookPart = z.infer<typeof HookPartSchema>;
```

Add to `ToolCallPartSchema` (after the `timeoutMs` field):

```typescript
export const ToolCallPartSchema = z
  .object({
    // ... existing fields ...
    timeoutMs: z.number().optional().describe('Approval timeout duration in milliseconds'),
    hooks: z.array(HookPartSchema).optional(),
  })
  .openapi('ToolCallPart');
```

### 5. Add type re-exports to types.ts

In `packages/shared/src/types.ts`, add to the first export block (from `'./schemas.js'`):

```typescript
export type {
  // ... existing types ...
  CompactBoundaryEvent,
  HookStartedEvent,
  HookProgressEvent,
  HookResponseEvent,
  HookPart,
} from './schemas.js';
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `StreamEventTypeSchema` enum includes `'hook_started'`, `'hook_progress'`, `'hook_response'`
- [ ] Three new Zod schemas (`HookStartedEventSchema`, `HookProgressEventSchema`, `HookResponseEventSchema`) are defined with `.openapi()` metadata
- [ ] All three schemas are included in the `StreamEventSchema` data union
- [ ] `ToolCallPartSchema` has an optional `hooks` field using `z.array(HookPartSchema).optional()`
- [ ] Types are re-exported from `packages/shared/src/types.ts`
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes across all packages
- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes

Add three new branches to the system message dispatch in `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sdk-event-mapper.ts` to handle `hook_started`, `hook_progress`, and `hook_response` SDK messages. Route tool-contextual hooks as new event types; route session-level hooks through existing `system_status` and `error` paths.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS constant

At module scope (after the imports, before `mapErrorCategory`), add:

```typescript
/** Hook events that correlate to a specific tool call and render inside ToolCallCard. */
const TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS = new Set([
  'PreToolUse',
  'PostToolUse',
  'PostToolUseFailure',
]);
```

### 2. Add three branches in the system message dispatch

Inside the `if (message.type === 'system' && 'subtype' in message)` block, after the `compact_boundary` branch (before the closing `}` of the system block at line 117), add:

```typescript
// Handle hook lifecycle events
if (message.subtype === 'hook_started') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const hookEvent = msg.hook_event as string;
  const isToolContextual = TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS.has(hookEvent);

  if (isToolContextual) {
    yield {
      type: 'hook_started',
      data: {
        hookId: msg.hook_id as string,
        hookName: msg.hook_name as string,
        hookEvent,
        toolCallId: toolState.currentToolId || null,
      },
    };
  } else {
    yield {
      type: 'system_status',
      data: { message: `Running hook "${msg.hook_name as string}"...` },
    };
  }
  return;
}

if (message.subtype === 'hook_progress') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const hookEvent = msg.hook_event as string;
  const isToolContextual = TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS.has(hookEvent);

  if (isToolContextual) {
    yield {
      type: 'hook_progress',
      data: {
        hookId: msg.hook_id as string,
        stdout: msg.stdout as string,
        stderr: msg.stderr as string,
      },
    };
  }
  // Session-level progress: silent (no useful output to show mid-execution)
  return;
}

if (message.subtype === 'hook_response') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const hookEvent = msg.hook_event as string;
  const isToolContextual = TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS.has(hookEvent);

  if (isToolContextual) {
    yield {
      type: 'hook_response',
      data: {
        hookId: msg.hook_id as string,
        hookName: msg.hook_name as string,
        exitCode: msg.exit_code as number | undefined,
        outcome: msg.outcome as 'success' | 'error' | 'cancelled',
        stdout: msg.stdout as string,
        stderr: msg.stderr as string,
      },
    };
  } else if ((msg.outcome as string) === 'error') {
    // Session-level failure: escalate to persistent error
    yield {
      type: 'error',
      data: {
        message: `Hook "${msg.hook_name as string}" failed (${hookEvent})`,
        code: 'hook_failure',
        category: 'execution_error',
        details: (msg.stderr as string) || (msg.stdout as string),
      },
    };
  }
  // Session-level success: silent (already shown via system_status on start)
  return;
}
```

## Testing

Add a new `describe('hook lifecycle events', ...)` block to `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/sdk-event-mapper.test.ts`. Use the existing `collectEvents`, `makeSession`, and `makeToolState` helpers.

First, add SDK message factory helpers at the top of the test file or in a dedicated section:

```typescript
function sdkHookStarted(hookId: string, hookName: string, hookEvent: string): SDKMessage {
  return {
    type: 'system',
    subtype: 'hook_started',
    hook_id: hookId,
    hook_name: hookName,
    hook_event: hookEvent,
    uuid: `uuid-${hookId}`,
    session_id: 'test-session',
  } as unknown as SDKMessage;
}

function sdkHookProgress(hookId: string, hookName: string, hookEvent: string, stdout: string, stderr: string): SDKMessage {
  return {
    type: 'system',
    subtype: 'hook_progress',
    hook_id: hookId,
    hook_name: hookName,
    hook_event: hookEvent,
    stdout,
    stderr,
    output: stdout + stderr,
    uuid: `uuid-${hookId}-progress`,
    session_id: 'test-session',
  } as unknown as SDKMessage;
}

function sdkHookResponse(hookId: string, hookName: string, hookEvent: string, outcome: string, exitCode?: number, stdout = '', stderr = ''): SDKMessage {
  return {
    type: 'system',
    subtype: 'hook_response',
    hook_id: hookId,
    hook_name: hookName,
    hook_event: hookEvent,
    output: stdout + stderr,
    stdout,
    stderr,
    exit_code: exitCode,
    outcome,
    uuid: `uuid-${hookId}-response`,
    session_id: 'test-session',
  } as unknown as SDKMessage;
}
```

Test cases:

1. **`hook_started` (tool-contextual) yields `hook_started` event** — Send a PreToolUse hook_started with `toolState.currentToolId = 'tool-123'`. Verify the yielded event has `type: 'hook_started'` with `hookId`, `hookName`, `hookEvent: 'PreToolUse'`, `toolCallId: 'tool-123'`.

2. **`hook_started` (session-level) yields `system_status` event** — Send a SessionStart hook_started. Verify `type: 'system_status'` with message containing the hook name.

3. **`hook_progress` (tool-contextual) yields `hook_progress` event** — Send PreToolUse hook_progress with stdout/stderr. Verify forwarded.

4. **`hook_progress` (session-level) yields nothing** — Send SessionStart hook_progress. Verify zero events yielded.

5. **`hook_response` (tool-contextual, success) yields `hook_response`** — Verify outcome 'success', exit code 0.

6. **`hook_response` (tool-contextual, error) yields `hook_response`** — Verify outcome 'error' with stderr.

7. **`hook_response` (session-level, error) yields `error` event** — Verify `type: 'error'` with `code: 'hook_failure'`, `category: 'execution_error'`, and stderr in details.

8. **`hook_response` (session-level, success) yields nothing** — Silent on success.

9. **`hook_started` with empty `currentToolId` yields `hook_started` with `toolCallId: null`** — Set `toolState.currentToolId = ''`, send PreToolUse hook_started, verify `toolCallId: null`.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `TOOL_CONTEXTUAL_HOOK_EVENTS` constant defined at module scope
- [ ] `hook_started` with tool-contextual `hook_event` yields `hook_started` event with `toolCallId` from `toolState.currentToolId`
- [ ] `hook_started` with session-level `hook_event` yields `system_status` event
- [ ] `hook_progress` with tool-contextual `hook_event` yields `hook_progress` event
- [ ] `hook_progress` with session-level `hook_event` is silent (no events)
- [ ] `hook_response` with tool-contextual `hook_event` yields `hook_response` event
- [ ] `hook_response` with session-level error yields `error` event with `code: 'hook_failure'`
- [ ] `hook_response` with session-level success is silent
- [ ] Empty `currentToolId` produces `toolCallId: null`
- [ ] All 9 unit tests pass
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes

Add the `HookState` interface to `chat-types.ts`, extend `ToolCallState` with a `hooks` field, add `orphanHooksRef` to `use-chat-session.ts`, add `findHookById` helper and three new switch cases (`hook_started`, `hook_progress`, `hook_response`) to `stream-event-handler.ts`, and modify the `tool_call_start` case to drain the orphan buffer.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add HookState interface to chat-types.ts

In `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/chat-types.ts`, add after the `ToolCallState` interface:

```typescript
/** State for a single hook execution lifecycle, attached to a parent ToolCallState. */
export interface HookState {
  hookId: string;
  hookName: string;
  hookEvent: string;
  status: 'running' | 'success' | 'error' | 'cancelled';
  stdout: string;
  stderr: string;
  exitCode?: number;
}
```

Extend `ToolCallState` with an optional `hooks` field:

```typescript
export interface ToolCallState {
  toolCallId: string;
  toolName: string;
  input: string;
  result?: string;
  progressOutput?: string;
  status: 'pending' | 'running' | 'complete' | 'error';
  interactiveType?: 'approval' | 'question';
  questions?: QuestionItem[];
  answers?: Record<string, string>;
  timeoutMs?: number;
  /** Hook executions attached to this tool call (PreToolUse, PostToolUse, etc.) */
  hooks?: HookState[];
}
```

### 2. Add orphanHooksRef to StreamEventDeps and use-chat-session.ts

In `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/stream-event-handler.ts`, add to the `StreamEventDeps` interface:

```typescript
interface StreamEventDeps {
  // ... existing fields ...
  orphanHooksRef: React.MutableRefObject<HookState[]>;
}
```

Add the import for `HookState`:

```typescript
import type { ChatMessage, ToolCallState, HookState, TransportErrorInfo } from './chat-types';
```

Add the import for new event types:

```typescript
import type {
  // ... existing imports ...
  HookStartedEvent,
  HookProgressEvent,
  HookResponseEvent,
} from '@dorkos/shared/types';
```

In `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts`, add:

```typescript
const orphanHooksRef = useRef<HookState[]>([]);
```

Import `HookState` from `chat-types` (it should already be available via the existing import). Add `orphanHooksRef` to the `createStreamEventHandler` call:

```typescript
const streamEventHandler = useMemo(
  () =>
    createStreamEventHandler({
      // ... existing deps ...
      orphanHooksRef,
    }),
  [sessionId, setSystemStatusWithClear]
);
```

### 3. Add findHookById helper

In `stream-event-handler.ts`, inside `createStreamEventHandler`, add this helper alongside `findToolCallPart` and `findSubagentPart`:

```typescript
function findHookById(hookId: string): HookState | undefined {
  for (const part of currentPartsRef.current) {
    if (part.type === 'tool_call' && part.hooks) {
      const hook = part.hooks.find((h) => h.hookId === hookId);
      if (hook) return hook;
    }
  }
  return undefined;
}
```

### 4. Add three switch cases

In the `handleStreamEvent` function's switch statement, add before the `'system_status'` case:

```typescript
case 'hook_started': {
  const hook = data as HookStartedEvent;
  if (hook.toolCallId) {
    const existing = findToolCallPart(hook.toolCallId);
    if (existing) {
      existing.hooks = [
        ...(existing.hooks || []),
        {
          hookId: hook.hookId,
          hookName: hook.hookName,
          hookEvent: hook.hookEvent,
          status: 'running',
          stdout: '',
          stderr: '',
        },
      ];
      updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
    }
  } else {
    // Orphan hook (PreToolUse before tool_call_start) — buffer it
    orphanHooksRef.current.push({
      hookId: hook.hookId,
      hookName: hook.hookName,
      hookEvent: hook.hookEvent,
      status: 'running',
      stdout: '',
      stderr: '',
    });
  }
  break;
}
case 'hook_progress': {
  const hp = data as HookProgressEvent;
  const hookPart = findHookById(hp.hookId);
  if (hookPart) {
    hookPart.stdout = hp.stdout;
    hookPart.stderr = hp.stderr;
    updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
  }
  break;
}
case 'hook_response': {
  const hr = data as HookResponseEvent;
  const hookPart = findHookById(hr.hookId);
  if (hookPart) {
    hookPart.status = hr.outcome === 'success'
      ? 'success'
      : hr.outcome === 'cancelled'
        ? 'cancelled'
        : 'error';
    hookPart.exitCode = hr.exitCode;
    hookPart.stdout = hr.stdout;
    hookPart.stderr = hr.stderr;
    updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
  }
  break;
}
```

### 5. Modify tool_call_start to drain orphan buffer

Modify the existing `case 'tool_call_start'` to attach buffered orphan hooks:

```typescript
case 'tool_call_start': {
  const tc = data as ToolCallEvent;
  const orphans = orphanHooksRef.current.splice(0); // drain buffer
  currentPartsRef.current.push({
    type: 'tool_call',
    toolCallId: tc.toolCallId,
    toolName: tc.toolName,
    input: '',
    status: 'running',
    hooks: orphans.length > 0 ? orphans : undefined,
  });
  updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
  break;
}
```

Note: The `hooks` field needs to be present in the `MessagePart` type for tool_call parts. This is handled by the `ToolCallPartSchema` extension in Task 1.1.

### 6. Update deriveFromParts to propagate hooks

Update the `deriveFromParts` function to include `hooks` in the derived `ToolCallState`:

```typescript
export function deriveFromParts(parts: MessagePart[]): { content: string; toolCalls: ToolCallState[] } {
  const textSegments: string[] = [];
  const toolCalls: ToolCallState[] = [];
  for (const part of parts) {
    if (part.type === 'text') {
      textSegments.push(part.text);
    } else if (part.type === 'tool_call') {
      toolCalls.push({
        toolCallId: part.toolCallId,
        toolName: part.toolName,
        input: part.input || '',
        result: part.result,
        progressOutput: part.progressOutput,
        status: part.status,
        interactiveType: part.interactiveType,
        questions: part.questions,
        answers: part.answers,
        timeoutMs: part.timeoutMs,
        hooks: part.hooks,
      });
    }
  }
  return { content: textSegments.join('\n'), toolCalls };
}
```

### 7. Re-export HookState from use-chat-session.ts

Update the re-export line in `use-chat-session.ts`:

```typescript
export type { ChatMessage, ToolCallState, HookState, GroupPosition, MessageGrouping, ChatStatus, ChatSessionOptions, TransportErrorInfo } from './chat-types';
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `HookState` interface defined in `chat-types.ts` with `hookId`, `hookName`, `hookEvent`, `status`, `stdout`, `stderr`, `exitCode`
- [ ] `ToolCallState` has optional `hooks?: HookState[]` field
- [ ] `orphanHooksRef` initialized in `use-chat-session.ts` and passed to `createStreamEventHandler`
- [ ] `findHookById` helper searches across all tool call parts
- [ ] `hook_started` with `toolCallId` adds hook to existing tool call's hooks array
- [ ] `hook_started` without `toolCallId` buffers to `orphanHooksRef`
- [ ] `hook_progress` updates hook's stdout/stderr by hookId
- [ ] `hook_response` updates hook's status, exitCode, stdout, stderr
- [ ] `tool_call_start` drains orphan buffer and attaches to new tool call
- [ ] `deriveFromParts` propagates hooks field
- [ ] `HookState` re-exported from `use-chat-session.ts`
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes

Add unit tests for the three new hook handler cases and the orphan hook attachment logic in the stream event handler.

## Implementation Steps

Create or append to `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/__tests__/stream-event-handler.test.ts`. This test file tests `createStreamEventHandler` directly by providing mock deps.

```typescript
/**
 * @vitest-environment jsdom
 */
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { createStreamEventHandler, deriveFromParts } from '../stream-event-handler';
import type { HookState } from '../chat-types';
import type { MessagePart } from '@dorkos/shared/types';

function makeDeps() {
  const currentPartsRef = { current: [] as MessagePart[] };
  const assistantCreatedRef = { current: true };
  const orphanHooksRef = { current: [] as HookState[] };
  const setMessages = vi.fn();
  const setError = vi.fn();
  const setStatus = vi.fn();
  const setSessionStatus = vi.fn();
  const setEstimatedTokens = vi.fn();
  const setStreamStartTime = vi.fn();
  const setIsTextStreaming = vi.fn();
  const setRateLimitRetryAfter = vi.fn();
  const setIsRateLimited = vi.fn();
  const setSystemStatus = vi.fn();

  return {
    currentPartsRef,
    assistantCreatedRef,
    orphanHooksRef,
    sessionStatusRef: { current: null },
    streamStartTimeRef: { current: null },
    estimatedTokensRef: { current: 0 },
    textStreamingTimerRef: { current: null },
    isTextStreamingRef: { current: false },
    thinkingStartRef: { current: null },
    rateLimitClearRef: { current: null },
    setMessages,
    setError,
    setStatus,
    setSessionStatus,
    setEstimatedTokens,
    setStreamStartTime,
    setIsTextStreaming,
    setRateLimitRetryAfter,
    setIsRateLimited,
    setSystemStatus,
    sessionId: 'test-session',
    onTaskEventRef: { current: undefined },
    onSessionIdChangeRef: { current: undefined },
    onStreamingDoneRef: { current: undefined },
  };
}

describe('stream-event-handler hook lifecycle', () => {
  let deps: ReturnType<typeof makeDeps>;
  let handler: ReturnType<typeof createStreamEventHandler>;
  const assistantId = 'assistant-1';

  beforeEach(() => {
    deps = makeDeps();
    handler = createStreamEventHandler(deps as any);
  });

  it('hook_started adds hook to existing tool call hooks array', () => {
    // Set up a tool call part
    deps.currentPartsRef.current = [
      { type: 'tool_call', toolCallId: 'tc-1', toolName: 'Bash', input: '', status: 'running' } as MessagePart,
    ];

    handler('hook_started', {
      hookId: 'hook-1',
      hookName: 'pre-commit',
      hookEvent: 'PreToolUse',
      toolCallId: 'tc-1',
    }, assistantId);

    const toolPart = deps.currentPartsRef.current[0];
    expect(toolPart.type).toBe('tool_call');
    if (toolPart.type === 'tool_call') {
      expect(toolPart.hooks).toHaveLength(1);
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0]).toEqual(expect.objectContaining({
        hookId: 'hook-1',
        hookName: 'pre-commit',
        hookEvent: 'PreToolUse',
        status: 'running',
        stdout: '',
        stderr: '',
      }));
    }
    expect(deps.setMessages).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('hook_started without toolCallId buffers to orphanHooksRef', () => {
    handler('hook_started', {
      hookId: 'hook-orphan',
      hookName: 'pre-commit',
      hookEvent: 'PreToolUse',
      toolCallId: null,
    }, assistantId);

    expect(deps.orphanHooksRef.current).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(deps.orphanHooksRef.current[0].hookId).toBe('hook-orphan');
    // Should NOT trigger setMessages (no tool call to update)
    expect(deps.setMessages).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('hook_progress updates hook stdout and stderr', () => {
    // Set up tool call with a hook
    deps.currentPartsRef.current = [
      {
        type: 'tool_call', toolCallId: 'tc-1', toolName: 'Bash', input: '', status: 'running',
        hooks: [{ hookId: 'hook-1', hookName: 'pre-commit', hookEvent: 'PreToolUse', status: 'running', stdout: '', stderr: '' }],
      } as MessagePart,
    ];

    handler('hook_progress', {
      hookId: 'hook-1',
      stdout: 'checking files...',
      stderr: '',
    }, assistantId);

    const toolPart = deps.currentPartsRef.current[0];
    if (toolPart.type === 'tool_call') {
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0].stdout).toBe('checking files...');
    }
    expect(deps.setMessages).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('hook_response marks hook status based on outcome', () => {
    deps.currentPartsRef.current = [
      {
        type: 'tool_call', toolCallId: 'tc-1', toolName: 'Bash', input: '', status: 'running',
        hooks: [{ hookId: 'hook-1', hookName: 'pre-commit', hookEvent: 'PreToolUse', status: 'running', stdout: '', stderr: '' }],
      } as MessagePart,
    ];

    handler('hook_response', {
      hookId: 'hook-1',
      hookName: 'pre-commit',
      exitCode: 1,
      outcome: 'error',
      stdout: '',
      stderr: 'trailing whitespace found',
    }, assistantId);

    const toolPart = deps.currentPartsRef.current[0];
    if (toolPart.type === 'tool_call') {
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0].status).toBe('error');
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0].exitCode).toBe(1);
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0].stderr).toBe('trailing whitespace found');
    }
    expect(deps.setMessages).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });

  it('orphan hooks attach to next tool_call_start', () => {
    // Buffer an orphan hook
    deps.orphanHooksRef.current = [
      { hookId: 'hook-orphan', hookName: 'pre-commit', hookEvent: 'PreToolUse', status: 'running', stdout: '', stderr: '' },
    ];

    handler('tool_call_start', {
      toolCallId: 'tc-new',
      toolName: 'Edit',
      status: 'running',
    }, assistantId);

    const toolPart = deps.currentPartsRef.current[0];
    if (toolPart.type === 'tool_call') {
      expect(toolPart.hooks).toHaveLength(1);
      expect(toolPart.hooks![0].hookId).toBe('hook-orphan');
    }
    // Orphan buffer should be drained
    expect(deps.orphanHooksRef.current).toHaveLength(0);
  });
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `hook_started` with toolCallId adds hook to tool call's hooks array
